                <h1>The Evolution of Tesla: A Brief History</h1>
                <p>Tesla, founded in 2003 by Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning, revolutionized the automotive industry with electric vehicles. In 2004, Elon Musk joined as chairman and transformed Tesla, launching the Roadster in 2008, followed by the Model S, Model X, Model 3, and Model Y. Tesla's innovations include advancements in battery technology, Autopilot features, and sustainable energy solutions, firmly establishing the brand as a leader in electric mobility.</p>
